epgy university mathematics m152 overview courses ohs summer schools apply and register home software research news contact epgy login course catalog mathematics university level m152 number theory lectures lessons exercises homework exams textbook epgy number theory m152 euclid's algorithm fundamental theorems on divisibility prime numbers congruence of numbers theorems of fermat euler wilson congruence of first and high degrees lagrange's theorem and applications residues of power quadratic residues introduction to theory of binary quadratic forms introduction to number theory and its applications the course focuses on theory and rigorous proofs of theorems and is available to students who have not yet begun the study of calculus the course is designed to take about 12 weeks to complete on average 3 units prerequisite m013 or equivalent
